main event: Sighting of an object observed by six persons pulling a trailer at Camp Irwin, California on September 26, 1960.
interesting points: The object was seen giving off smoke and had an estimated speed of 3000 feet per minute,The sighting lasted about 30 seconds and was described as being very fast at 400-450 mph,It was concluded that the sighting had all characteristics of a missile, but no definitive identification was made,No follow-up report was received after the initial sighting,Observers reported the object trailing flames of red and/or orange.
sighted object: an unidentified object resembling a missile
